Code Implementation Guidelines
Follow these strict rules when writing code:

Use early returns whenever possible to improve readability.
Always use TailwindCSS for styling—avoid external CSS or inline styles.
Use “class:” syntax instead of the ternary operator within class attributes when applicable.
Use descriptive names for variables, functions, and constants.
Event handler naming: Prefix with "handle", e.g., handleClick, handleInputChange, handleSubmit.
Accessibility first: Ensure that interactive elements include necessary attributes such as:
tabindex="0"
aria-label
onClick, onKeyDown
Use functional consts for state updates:
✅ const toggle = () => {...}
❌ function toggle() {...}
Type definitions: Use TypeScript types/interfaces where applicable.
This guideline ensures that all code is modern, scalable, readable, and maintainable while leveraging Vite, React, and TailwindCSS effectively.
